    "description": "CHIeru Co.,Ltd. engages in the production of ICT environments for teaching and learning in schools in Japan and internationally. The company's services include software and system products, teaching and learning resources, and strategic consulting for school ICT environments in primary and higher education. It offers InterCLASS Cloud, a web-based classroom management software, that facilitates collaborative learning using Google Workspace for Education; CaLabo EX, a computer-assisted digital language lab solution system, that supports all types of teaching materials; Tbridge, improves network bottlenecks with patented technology; and GLEXA, a learning system that offers e-learning features. The company was incorporated in 1997 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan. CHIeru Co.,Ltd. is a joint venture of Alps System Integration Co., Ltd. and Obunsha Co., Ltd."
